==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''meek'', [[meke]], borrowed from a Scandinavian source such as Old Norse [[mjúkr]], "soft".

===Pronunciation===
*''General American'' [[w:IPA|IPA]]/[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] /mik/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːk|-iːk]]

===Adjective===
'''meek''' (meeker, meekest)
# humble, modest, self-effacing

====Translations====
*Bulgarian: [[мек]] 
*Finnish: [[nöyrä]]
*Norwegian: [[blyg]]
*Spanish: [[manso]]

===Noun===
'''the meek'''
# People who are meek.
e.g "Blessed are the meek, for they shall inherit the earth" (Matthew chapter 5, verse 5)
